cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a method for detecting events in time-series data using a novel feature descriptor inspired by ideas in image processing. The method uses SVM-based, multi-sensor, supervised learning scenario, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using the technique on multiple standard time-series datasets, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
